item.item_description: Being a maths-enhancing hairpiece that endeavors to heighten the senses of any soul, be he a gentle-man of leisure deserving of such a thing, or a loathsome tiller of the earth of whom a beating would not go unwarranted.

item.name: The Brainiac Goggles
item.item_description: Being prescription shooting goggles that endeavor to relieve the eye from the reflection off one's gun barrel whilst also correcting Diplopia, Strabismus, 'Nervous Vision', Early-Onset Old-Eye, and several other varieties of structural defect.

item.name: Dr. Grordbort's Copper Crest
item.item_description: Being a water-soluble, highly poisonous copper crest offering mute testament to one's commitment to the sciences. Prolonged exposure may cause tissue putridity, muscle atrophy and bone softening in the infirm, elderly and those graced with child.

item.name: The Third Degree
item.item_description: Being a boon to tree-fellers, backwoodsmen and atom-splitters the world over, this miraculous matter-hewing device burns each individual molecule as it cleaves it.

item.name: The Phlogistinator
item.item_description: Being a revolutionary appliance capable of awakening the fire element phlogiston that exists in all combustible creatures, which is to say, all of them.

item.name: The Manmelter
item.item_description: Being a device that flouts conventional scientific consensus that the molecules composing the human body must be arranged "just so", and not, for example, across a square-mile radius.

item.name: The Moonman Backpack
item.item_description: Being a repository of the foundational ingredients necessary for a body to live a life of leisure in space—namely one part oxygen, one part mercury, and twelve parts laudanum.

item.name: The Bubble Pipe
item.item_description: Being an invention that achieves the humanitarian goal of all great men of science, from Lord Holland to the Duke of Wellington, to allow a true gentle-man to smoke a pipe in space.

item.name: Manniversary Giveaway Package
item.item_description:
From your fine friends at Mann Co., celebrating our one-year anniversary.
This contains a free sample from our fall lineup and can be opened from your backpack.

item.name: Your Worst Nightmare
item.item_description: This bandanna will teach you to eat things that would make a billy goat puke. Like another billy goat.

item.name: The One-Man Army
item.item_description: You send that many men against a bandanna like this, don't forget one thing: A good supply of body bags.

item.name: The Counterfeit Billycock
item.item_description: This hat is a spy.

item.name: The Outdoorsman
item.item_description: Chop wood. Eat syrup. Live in Canada. This hat lets you do it all.

item.name: The Tavish DeGroot Experience
item.item_description: Hey, Joe, where you going with that sticky launcher in your hand?

item.name: The Pencil Pusher
item.item_description: Measure twice, cut once, shoot first.

item.name: The Builder's Blueprints
item.item_description: Never bring a gun to a blueprint fight.

item.name: The Buccaneer's Bicorne
item.item_description: Hoist the mainsail! Buckle those swashes! Get into a swordfight! Pirate captains yell stuff like this all the time, and now you can too.

item.name: The Bootlegger
item.item_description: Amaze your friends! Impress women! Walk with a limp for life! It's grotesque!

item.name: The Scottish Handshake
item.item_description: Your enemies will think you're making peace, right up until the terrifying moment that their hand is very seriously cut! Here's the trick: It's a broken bottle!

item.name: A Whiff of the Old Brimstone
item.item_name: A Whiff of the Old Brimstone
item.item_description: Your enemies will clap in delight at the cartoonish innocence of these old-timey bombs, making it that much sweeter when you blow their arms off.

item.name: The Salty Dog
item.item_description: Get all of a boat captain's respect without the crushing responsibility of actually captaining a boat or the enormous amount of ongoing maintenance a boat requires!

item.name: The Little Buddy
item.item_description: People will think you're in the Navy. But the joke is on them, BECAUSE YOU'RE NOT! That is just one possible benefit of this tricky hat.

item.name: The Gym Rat
item.item_description: Let's get physical. Physical.

item.name: The Hot Dogger
item.item_description: There's been a terrible explosion at the hot dog factory! That's what you can tell people, and they'll believe you because you will look like an expert on hot dogs.

item.name: The Birdcage
item.item_description: Everyone will wonder what the secret meaning of this mysterious hat is. The secret is you're an idiot.

item.name: The Surgeon's Stahlhelm
item.item_description: Technically, field medics are protected as noncombatants under the Geneva Convention. The next time you get shot be sure to tell your killer. It's a conversation starter!

item.name: The Backwards Ballcap
item.item_description: Stick it to Major League Baseball by not wearing their hat the right way.

item.name: The Crocodile Smile
item.item_description: How many crocodiles had to die to make this necklace? A lot. That's the point.

item.name: Flair!
item.item_description:
Show enthusiasm! For your favorite things!
Custom decals can be applied to this item.

item.name: Couvre Corner
item.item_description: Sometimes we put some jokes in these descriptions. But, no joke: This looks good. Really sharp.

item.name: The Surgeon's Stethoscope
item.item_description: Look like you know what you're doing when you pronounce people dead.

item.name: L'Inspecteur
item.item_description: Nobody is not scared of a policeman from France. That is why this hat is so effective.

item.name: Photo Badge
item.item_description:
Discourage identity theft.
Custom decals can be applied to this item.

item.name: Clan Pride
item.item_description:
Because it's cheaper and less painful than a tattoo.
Custom decals can be applied to this item.

item.name: The Swagman's Swatter
item.item_description: This is the best hat. We couldn't say it if it weren't true. This one's the best.

item.name: The Flamboyant Flamenco
item.item_description: Help your enemies celebrate Day of the Dead by wearing this hat and then killing them.

item.name: The Virtual Reality Headset
item.item_description: With these on, you can pretend you're winning.

item.name: The Spectre's Spectacles
item.item_description: So mysterious. So deadly. So nearsighted.

item.name: The Stereoscopic Shades
item.item_description: If you close an eye, one of the teams will disappear. So don't do that.

item.name: The Hat With No Name
item.item_description: A nameless hat for a nameless man.

item.name: The Cremator's Conscience
item.item_description: 'Burn him with fire!' 'No, burn him with fire, then hit him with an axe!'

item.name: The Hermes
item.item_description: Don't shoot the messenger. Actually, go ahead and try. Can't be done, pal! Too fast!

item.name: Point and Shoot
item.item_description: The next time someone accuses you of not being a real wizard because you refuse to (read: can't) do spells, poke them in the eye with this magically blinding pointy hat and run.

item.name: War Head
item.item_description: Protect your thought-horde from dragons, sorcery, and other make-believe dangers with this spiky lead battle-mask.

item.name: Dr. Grordbort's Silver Crest
item.item_description: Being a highly malleable, thoroughly combustible silver crest that declares one's commitment, and intention, to immolate all creatures on God's Earth.

item.name: The Dashin' Hashshashin
item.item_description: When you need to go deep undercover, one disguise is not enough! Put a hood over that ski-mask, then wrap a towel around it. Boldly announce to the world that you are inconspicuous!

item.name: The Sharp Dresser
item.item_description: Every merc's crazy for a sharp-dressed man. With 15th century murder-knives extruding from his cufflinks.

item.name: The Top Notch
item.item_description: Welcome to a secret society so exclusive it makes the Illuminati look like a Costco. How exclusive? You are the only member. This is the only item of its kind in all of existence. So don't craft it, Miney.

item.name: The Ornament Armament
item.item_description: Just a like the Soldier's actual grenades, these shiny glass baubles are purely ornamental.

item.name: The Sandvich Safe
item.item_description: Keep sandvich safe with sandvich safe. Okay, is good, no more description. Buy.

item.name: The Head Warmer
item.item_description: This incinerator's insulator keeps your head a perfect 105 degrees, while muffling the hallucinations brought on by wearing a hat that slowly cooks your brain.

item.name: The Outback Intellectual
item.item_description: Argyle. Pipe-smoking. Individually, they make you look like an idiot. Together, they make you look smart AND stylish! Just like Umberto Eco!

item.name: The Itsy Bitsy Spyer
item.item_description: Is that a miniature Spy in your pocket, or are you just happy to OH GOD STOP HITTING ME!

item.name: The All-Father
item.item_description: Throughout the history of civilization, the white beard has come to symbolize wisdom and status. Show the world it's possible to be bearded AND stupid with this Heavy- and Soldier-specific face-nest. Shove it, civilization!

item.name: The Wrap Assassin
item.item_description: These lovely festive ornaments are so beautifully crafted, your enemies are going to want to see them close up. Indulge them by batting those fragile glass bulbs into their eyes at 90 mph.

item.name: The Spy-cicle
item.item_description: It's the perfect gift for the man who has everything: an icicle driven into their back. Even rich people can't buy that in stores.

attribute.name: become fireproof on hit by fire

item.name: The Kringle Collection
item.item_description: Do the snow-pants dance with this stylish holiday ensemble from famed Arctic designer Kristoff Kringle.

item.name: The Jingle Belt
item.item_description: Slay-bells will be ringing in the slow-roasted ears of your burn victims.

item.name: The Big Elfin Deal
item.item_description: You ask me if I wanna be a dentist one more time, pal, I'm gonna kick your teeth in.

item.name: The Bootie Time
item.item_description: You dasher! You dancer! You prancer! You VIXEN! Pull Santa's sleigh all by yourself, you sexy little man.

item.name: Spirit Of Giving
item.item_description: The more gifts you give away, the bigger your heart will get! Get what gift-givers call "the Smissmass spirit," and what cardiologists call hypertrophic cardiomyopathy.

item.name: The Holiday Punch
item.item_description: Be the life of the war party with these laugh-inducing punch-mittens.

item.name: The Nine-Pipe Problem
item.item_description: In the time it takes you to read this description, I've already ubered a heavy, captured your base, solved a crime, and smoked three pipes.

item.name: The B.M.O.C.
item.item_description: Be the Big Man of Christmas with this fur-fringed pom-pom hat!

item.name: The Holiday Headcase
item.item_description: Merry Smissmas, everyone! May all your miscellaneous holidays be happy (or somber, depending on your cultural traditions) with this ultra-rare TF item, donated by Steam User BANG!

item.name: The Full Head of Steam
item.item_description: You never took a break from cp_foundry, and now you can prove it with the actual steam whistle used to call the breaks you never took!

item.name: The Stocking Stuffer
item.item_description: No need to hang this stocking over the mantle. It's already stuffed. Thanks for nothing, Santa.

item.name: The Brown Bomber
item.item_description: Celebrate Canada's birthday, on whatever day that happens, with this commemorative Canadian Prime Minister's ceremonial dress hat.

item.name: The Ebenezer
item.item_description: If you are visited by one piece of spectral headwear this night, make it the Ghost of Christmas Hats, donated in true Smissmass spirit by Steam User Jacen.

item.item_description: Let's see you do that again, Private.

item.name: The Warsworn Helmet
item.item_description: Whether you're a mercenary in the granaries and gravel pits of the Badlands or an immense fantasy world, this helmet tells potential employers everything they need to know: You will do horrible, horrible things for money.

item.name: The Bolgan
item.item_description: Protect the all-important empty socket part of your face while giving enemies an irresistible target: unimportant exposed parts like your mouth, nose and generally all the non-socket parts of your face.

item.name: The Bolgan Family Crest
item.item_description: This stylish bronze badge lets people know that at some crucial point in your family genealogy, one of your family members became intimately involved with a monster cyclops.

item.name: The Boston Boom-Bringer
item.item_description: Walkin' down the street to the hardcore beat while his Mann Co. boom vibrates the concrete.

item.name: Aladdin's Private Reserve
item.item_description: Originally owned by some punk kid in Syria, this Arabian wish-granter is a lamp full of liquid courage. Simply rub, think liquory thoughts, and pour. Warning: don't think about anything else while rubbing, or you might not get booze.

item.name: The Snapped Pupil
item.item_description: Be honest, lads. Ye cannae even tell, can ye?

item.name: Daily Duel Winner Reward Hat
item.item_description: Congratulations on winning more duels yesterday than any other TF2 player! Wear this with pride before it changes hands tomorrow!

item.name: Daily Gift Giver Reward Hat
item.item_description: Congratulations on giving out more gifts yesterday than any other TF2 player! Wear this with pride before it changes hands tomorrow!

item.name: Daily Map Stamp Reward Hat
item.item_description: Congratulations on doing more yesterday to support the TF2 map-making community through map stamps than anyone else! Wear this with pride before it changes hands tomorrow!

item.name: The Merc Medal
item.item_description: There exists an agency so secret that only three people on the planet even know of its existence. This is the medal they give each other when one of them does a great job.

item.name: The Battle Bob
item.item_description: Simple and elegant, this slimming hair helmet will bring out the natural contours of your fearsome war face.

item.name: The Bushman's Boonie
item.item_description: Everybody knows that the head part of your body needs twice as much camouflage as all the other parts. Ask anyone in the army and they'll kill you and hide the body, because that widely-known information is CLASSIFIED.

item.name: The Conquistador
item.item_description: Make Spanish history come alive with this authentic conquistador's helmet, excavated from the actual grave of a sixteenth century French cosplayer.

item.name: The Fast Learner
item.item_description: Read a book – or at least look like you can – with this vintage educational ensemble. Be the B.M.O.C. (Big Mouth on Campus) of your own make-believe Ivy League!

item.name: The Black Rose
item.item_description: Slay it with flowers.

item.name: Store Purchase Promotion Package
item.item_description: This bag contains one free item from the Mann Co. store! You can open it from your backpack!

item.name: The Teufort Tooth Kicker
item.item_description: These steel-toed dogs were scientifically engineered (in a wind tunnel) by America's foremost authorities on mouth-kicking to perfectly fit the inside of an idiot's mouth.

item.name: The Waxy Wayfinder
item.item_description: Finally live your life like a candle in the wind. (Wind not included.)

item.name: The Scrap Pack
item.item_description: Why let your front have all the fun? Add more junk to the upper part of your trunk with this selection from the finest junkyards in Paris.

item.name: The Texas Half-Pants
item.item_description: It's pants... Texas Style! These crotchless leather leggings are perfect if you already own pants. Note: To be used as auxiliary pants only. Please do not employ as primary source of pants.

item.name: The Bolt Action Blitzer
item.item_description: Take a knee, boys. Now, any helmet will protect your head when you're wearing it – but what about when you're NOT? The Bolt Action Blitzer solves that problem by securing it to your skull with three one-and-a-quarter-inch coarse-thread galvanized crown bolts. Make sure it's in your favorite color, 'cause you WILL be buried in it.

item.name: The Toss-Proof Towel
item.item_description: Make sure you never throw in the towel, even accidentally, by keeping it nice and close, where it can't run off and surrender like a coward when you're not looking.

item.name: The Fruit Shoot
item.item_description: This fun, all-ages activity brings history alive! All you need is a bow, an arrow, an apple, and an idiot.

item.name: The Front Runner
item.item_description: This commemorative sweatband is a loving tribute to the heroes – and we don't use that word lightly – who live their lives like sweaty candles in the wind.

item.name: The Triclops
item.item_description: Fool your enemies into thinking you can see better! Here's the trick: You won't be able to see at all!

item.name: The Flamingo Kid
item.item_description: Are you man enough to wear this brightly colored cowboy hat? Just in case you're not, we slapped a half-a-skull on it to ease you into the exciting new world of wearing this hat.

item.name: World Traveler
item.item_description: Given to generous souls who have donated to community map makers. The effect will only be visible while on a map that has been donated towards!
